The paper deals with object detection using CNNs and click supervision, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. The use of CAMs and proposal selection algorithms also suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and multimedia (cs.MM) subfields. Additionally, the paper involves image-level annotations and ground-truth generation, which could be relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) as well.
